Package ibo1.Protocol

Class ChessEngine

java.lang.Object
ibo1.Protocol.ChessEngine
public class ChessEngine extends Object
ChessEngine - Class that represents ChessEngine communications

It defines the commands and errors and communication with the ROS system for chess moves. Direct representation would be the ChessWrapperNode.cpp in the ROS system.

Version:
0.1 ( Initial development )., 1.0 ( Initial release ).
Author:
Omar Ibrahim

    • stopChessEngine

      public void stopChessEngine(IRCClient ircClient) throws IOException, ProtocolException
      Stops the chess engine. This is used to abort a game. If a game is not stopped it will currently not work to start a new game.
      Parameters:
      ircClient - ircClient to be used
      Throws:
      IOException - thrown by sending and receiving the buffer
      ProtocolException - thrown if returned cmd does not match expected or if chess engine doesn't exist.
